tip.text: It's high end place so you have to dress somewhat properly. But fish is obviously amazing so still worth it.
Definitely scallops. It's marinated so well then baked perfectly with cheese on it. Can keep eating it.

formattedAddress: San Francisco (e/ Cl 67 E & Cl 68 E)

tip.text: Lots of great veggies but mushroom is definitely the best. Smokey cheese makes mushroom as good as it could ever be. One reason to keep coming back here.
Great seafood spot. Ask for razor clam when it's available.
My favorite in New York. Clean, comfortable and great service. In the middle of most happening LES. Avoid room just above 16F that is looking to the Purple. You won't be able to sleep in the weekend.
Their seasonal plate features seasonal vegetable are b Japan. Beautiful, tasty and healthy. Especially the one in Spring.

formattedAddress: 六本木6-10-1 (森タワーウエストウォーク 5F)
location.crossStreet: 森タワーウエストウォーク 5F

venue.name: やさい家めい 六本木ヒルズ店

tip.text: Moroccan scramble is a perfect breakfast to start the day powerful. Big portion.
Take dark and narrow stairs right on the left of ramen shop then this tiny lamb restaurant inside the dark door. Choose from the course. You can enjoy a series of quality lamb BBQ in every style.
Seafood bowl comes with a large portion but you can enjoy till last piece with a little salty but very rich broth.
Relaxing room, great view rooftop bar, perfect location to enjoy cool vibe of DTLA.
Stringhe di Funghi is the must order for brunch. Mushroom, prosciutto, egg and arugula tastes perfect together. Potato also tastes great and crispy.
Carpaccio for starter. You can't underestimate it as carpaccio. Unique and incredibly tasty.
Creative and flavorful. Each dish from starter, main to dessert is fulfilling.
Lamb is incredible. Meat and fat are both tender and cook to the perfection.
Oil sardine, octopus over a glass of red sangria makes it a great Sunday afternoon.
Great lounge that worth arriving earlier. Wide selection of foods and drinks, especially 4 different beers from the servers. Great massaging corner. Shoe shine service.

formattedAddress: 羽田空港2-6-5 (国際線ターミナル)

venue.name: JAL First Class Lounge - International Terminal (JAL ファーストクラスラウンジ - 国際線ターミナル)

tip.text: Unfortunately razor clam is not available all the time. But there are plenty other or all other dishes to make up for. Bone marrow. Creamy eggs. Fluke. Must sit at the counter table.
Carpaccio is great, fresh saint jacques comes with a hint of spice. This place has chairs at counter table so you can sit and enjoy all the fresh seafood tapas.
Very reasonable but tasty tapas and wine. Carpaccio at €6.50 is a must order. Mushroom is something you can't miss.
They have great fish and vegetables bbq on top of great meat selection. Sardine and Artichoke are especially great.
Baked eggs is obviously amazing on its own but gets even better by tasting it with slices of avocado. It's a must order.
Choose premium pork for shabu shabu and enjoy both premium and standard pork. They bring 4 different tasty dips but make sure you try it with salt and scallion first. Even better than dips.

formattedAddress: 六本木7-5-11 (カサグランデミワ 2F)

venue.name: Butagumi Shabuan (豚組 しゃぶ庵)

tip.text: Be bold and make a reservation of wild turtle course. You will know amazing Japanese dishes you have been missed in your life. Eat it raw, fried, cooked and drink it. You will come back once tried.

location.crossStreet: ソワレド銀座弥生ビルＢ１Ｆ
formattedAddress: 銀座7-6-19 (ソワレド銀座弥生ビルＢ１Ｆ)

tip.text: At this dim sum style restaurant, everything they bring is tempting but you must ask for dumpling if they didn't come around. $3 but it's 100 times satisfaction guaranteed.
Start from focaccia and octopus salumi. You may feel you had all the great tastes but you aren't. Orecchiette is one of the best pasta you may have then main is waiting. Must come here hungry.
Cool but still feels like home. Guitar for whoever want to play something.
Wide range of machines, many resting spaces, amazing view of Petco park, relaxing outdoor pool. Everything you can look for the gym is here. $20 daily pass for selected hotel guests.
Sprout pizza is amazing but Spicy honey is even great. A hint of spiciness add a depth to this simply tasty pizza. You can't miss vegetable dishes from either starter or side menu.
Unlike other places, they don't steam cook the eel so it is much more crispy despite soft inside. Once you love it, you can't go other eel places any longer.
Their Spanish brunch is quite nice. Egg Benedict becomes much more interesting with their Spanish twist to it.
You choose which taco to go at order then you choose flour or corn at the kitchen. You can mix flour and corn. Flour tastes a little better to me.
Knowledgeable staff will help you choose perfect wine that matches to each dish. Seabass starter and fillet are both excellent dishes.
Comte cheese Soufflé may be too simple dish but you won't regret by it's lingering taste of mote cheese in its soft texture of soufflé in each bite.
Great service and sophisticated decor in the middle of Opera, Pyramides and Madeleine.
Steak tartare seems to be famous and indeed amazing. But you can't miss burrata starter. Fresh and sweet.
Start with cocktail mixto then lamb belly wonton is a must. Main is nice but starter has more interesting dishes.
Great feel of weekend in France. No matter if it's weekend or weekdays.Chèvre salad is very nice.

contact.facebookName: Monsieur Marcel Gourmet Market and Restaurants

tip.text: Bon appetite from chef's table. Fluke is great. Mushroom can never be missed but it is pasta that brings me back to this restaurant no matter how long the wait is.
Porchetta tastes perfect. Crispness and richness of pork taste come together perfectly.
Smashed beans is great when mixed with poached egg. You may want to have 2 poached eggs to enjoy this great marching till end.
Make sure to choose butterfish. Bitterly taste, sweetness and accent of herb match together and make it a perfect starter.
Spices in the water, sangria and green salad...it all comes together gently and make it great dining experience. Side green salad with dip is surprisingly tasty.
You will love zuke don more when it comes as combination with ramen. Ramen may need a bit more broth but make good light lunch set.
Go for lunch. Go for pizza. Cicinielli is definitely the best.
Window side tables are usually booked but you can get it after 11pm to look down Seoul river and city beyond over drinks.

It has all the good elements of 5 star hotels in Asia. Incredible buffet, well equipped fitness center and top floor bar makes it the perfect destination. Not in the central Seoul but  does it matter?
You can select tapas from showcase or order from menu. Anchovies and sardines are cooked to order.
Love the decor. Portion looks huge but you can easily finish. Chicken was great.
Tiradito choices change regularly but anything with white fish with Japanese herb or flavor is always amazing.
Ceviche and paella w sea urchin source are best. Looking over kitchen and seeing how they make the plate is one of the fun here.
Porchetta is great for a dinner and amazing for brunch here.

formattedAddress: 53 Great Jones St (btwn Lafayette St & Bowery)

tip.text: The place will be filled with people after 5 or 6pm. Perfect place to drink over sunset of the downtown skyscrapers.
Crispy and juicy. Simple and not over spiced. Can understand why so popular. Choose ice tea sweetened or non sweetened.
Steak is great but I really loved pork.
All what you like is on the pan with perfect ensemble.
Simplest pasta is often the tastiest at the best restaurants. Perfectly cooked spaghetti with cheese and black pepper. The best.

formattedAddress: 53 Great Jones St (btwn Lafayette St & Bowery)

tip.text: Simplest is often tastiest. Spaghetti with tomato and basil was very sophisticated taste that doesn't need to shout loud.
Having Samgaetang and Korean bathhouse makes you as healthy as you can be in the cold winter in Seoul.
Noodle looks too much if you are not very hungry but you are completely wrong. Add kimchi and lots of chili on the table. You may even want to add up one more noodle.
Quail egg is a great starter. Octopus takes long to be served but worth the wait.
Great lasagna and pasta. Polipo is my favorite. I wonder how they can cook octopus so soft inside. No chewiness at all.

formattedAddress: 7313 Beverly Blvd (btwn Fuller Ave. and Poinsettia Pl.)
location.crossStreet: btwn Fuller Ave. and Poinsettia Pl.

tip.text: Chicken is definitely fantastic but this place changed my perception about gnocchi and made me think gnocchi can be extremely tasty.
Fried olive can't be missed. Salmon either. Even crowded, wait to be seated at dinner table than bar table. Fancy interior to entertain your dinner inside.
You never know how much is each but still best to leave to chef choice. Cho-chin is one of highlight. Grotesque I know but the look is nothing when you taste it's richness of egg yolk.
Too good hotel to stay only for Universal studio visit. The Front Yard, pool and bar, fireplace at the lobby, all makes this hotel very comfortable and pleasant stay.
Nice rooftop pool but it's this bathtub that makes this hotel my regular place in Jakarta.

formattedAddress: Jalan M. H. Thamrin No. 1 (Bundaran HI, Menteng)

tip.text: Pork hock is crispy and juicy. But the vege are great and I really liked broccoli rabe.
It's like eating xiao long bao. Tasty juice comes out at each bite.
Series of creative and very tasty dishes. Squid is pleasant surprise. Both soft middle part and crispy part go really well with lots of other ingredient and ink sauce.

You get worried when you first see the reception. North tower or south tower, not much difference. You get to the room and it all changes. Very comfortable, relaxing and spacious room in front of you.
They have so many good stuff to choose for brunch. So sit back, order beignets, sip one of their Bloody Mary and look around other people table.
Every dish is visually entertaining. Using lots of Japanese ingredients and flavors to make each dish unique and flavorful. You would specially enjoy that with Maitake one in each bite.

formattedAddress: 1525 Fillmore St (btwn O'Farrell St & Geary Blvd)

tip.text: Top grade hormone run out quickly. Fresh and juice into your mouth. Once tasted, you don't even need red meat or marble fat beef. Enjoy with happy hour deal serving Suntory Premium Malts at 200 yen.

venue.name: ホルモン でですけ

tip.text: You wanna try each different meat but churrasco de lomo is especially good.
Chic, beautiful, comfortable hotel. You even want to stay here longer rather than going out for sightseeing.
Liver and paprika one are however the must try.
Not always you know what you are eating. Doesn't matter, just leave it to the staff as you will definitely enjoy interesting but great taste that you can enjoy only here.
Many good small dishes. Lamb skewer is especially good.
Branzino is my must choice these days. With vegetable on top, this is the perfect dish to appreciate great foods both from ocean and land.
Raw fish section is so tempting and it's worth picking 2 or 3 from here but never skip shrimp toast.
You may ever expect you could have this good quality Thai foods in West Hollywood. Or in LA. Or in...
If you came afternoon, better not expect you can get a bed even if you leave the name. You can still soak in the pool over drinks.
Choose Dave. It's big but it's so good and you find yourself finishing it so quick.
Cool hotel room and great rooftop terrace or gym. But it also offers lots of workspace both at ground floor and at mezzanine looking downstairs.

venue.name: citizenM Hotel New York Times Square

tip.text: It's crowded but you can still find a chair.
Open only to the hotel guest. Looking up the skyscraper and down the Times Square in a quiet modern deco bar.
Another great breakfast spot with tasty coffee near Japan town. White egg sandwich is very tasty.
Each portion is not that big so you can order and experience many different dishes. Merguez was extremely good among others.

formattedAddress: 1525 Fillmore St (btwn O'Farrell St & Geary Blvd)

tip.text: Great selection of wine and cheese. You can find Nancy's Camembert here.
You can start with tasty raw fish dishes but the main is the hot pot. Enjoy topping as you eat. Chicken balls, dumplings, fried tofu and spinach. They all goes really well with this unique soup.

venue.name: 博多 いずみ田 中目黒店

tip.text: Soft and more sophisticated type unagi plate. Good that unakimo soup is already included. You get 400 yen surcharge on top of what you order.
Sashimi for starter. Main for Oyster blade with truffle sauce.
Place that justifies beef tartar and beer for breakfast.

Cheap but good quality eat in Ginza. Hard to find. Go inside small lane next to Mergellina. Ask lunch set (teisyoku) with tofu and chicken soup (tori tofu). Comes with only specific tataki sashimi set

formattedAddress: 銀座2-3-4 (並木通り 路地入ル)
location.crossStreet: 並木通り 路地入ル

venue.name: 大衆割烹 三州屋 銀座店

tip.text: Very good and 'more' reasonable eel place in Ginza area. Close early so be careful.
reasonable price meatball and drinks. healthy and tasty salad. only if meatball came a little more hotter like just out from oven..was even better.
No matter if you take standing table or counter table of each shop, you can order the same dishes.
Top floor room. Fantastic room with fantastic view.
All the vegetable plates are great, especially Okies but it's off season so out of menu in winter. For brunch, choose anything that comes with fried egg. The best fried egg I ever tasted.
Great breakfast spot to start a day. Great grilled sandwich. Egg, bacon, cheese and vege all cooked perfectly.
The same bar counter and chairs with its LA branch. Small dishes are good size for light lunch.
Shop at Conran then brunch at Aubaine.
Just indulge yourself. Great food over the choice of champagnes.
Public viewing of the game over the drink on the sunny day.
I love Blue Bottle Coffee from SF but this is as good as Blue Bottle.
They don't have sangria but they have tinto limone. Refreshing drink.
This is half portion.
Octopus Garcia. Soft, tender and lightly spiced.
Everything great but truffle burger is incredible.
35 Euro per bed. After spending a whole day, you would feel it was worth a spend. Their Asian beef salad is great refreshing taste under the sun.
Pasta is great but you can't miss seafood dishes for starter.
Sweet chilli or Spicy something. Inventive great cocktail. It's kind of drinking acai smoothie but with alcohol and lingering spiciness. Great.
Be prepared to walk all the long stairs but all the effort pays off. And beer just taste so great after all the walk.
Take a lift inside U Prince hotel. It's worth the visit to come just for a drink over great view.
Great place to escape from noise and just chill out over great cocktail and jewel like bottles over the counter. The great hidden place.
Specialty but not so expensive chicken place. Skewer, pot or sashimi, everything great. Special heart skewer, kokoro-nokori, is available for only 4-8 per day. Fatty and tasty.
Speck, mozzarella and oregano pizza. Buffalo mozzarella gives perfect essence to this crispy pizza.
Extensive choice of glass wine. Choose wine flights so you can enjoy 3 in one. You still have to choose from which wine flights to go though.
Salmon is exceptional. Cooked surface but inside is raw and tender.
Add fried egg on top of big salad.
Come earlier so you have more oyster options. Sashimi is also must try. You can enjoy each bite of this shellfish sashimi.
Pasta is amazing but don't miss side dish vegetable. Kale is great, Asian flavor in it.
4-7pm 7 dollar truffle burger is the must buy don't miss veal tonnato either.
Soft and gentle taste slowly wakes you up. Perfect for breakfast. Pot of black tea goes perfectly well with the toast.
Babette steak was tasty and healthy choice but the best was duck. Never had duck this soft and sensitively flavored. Perfect with 1.5$ per ounce wine.
Draft wine are great. Ask for tasting and choose your favorite. Mine was Cabernet Franc.
Winter...no, it's early summer.
Look far then look down.
Start with chicken liver. Taste like sweets. Menu keeps changing but capellini is always perfect choice. Get knocked out with spring cabbage pasta.
Sit at fireplace after spending a chilling SF day.
Choose some from vegetable section. Small portion but never disappoints you.

formattedAddress: 35 E 18th St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave S)

tip.text: If you want to sit properly but still want to enjoy quality cheap French dishes, this is your uokin.

venue.name: ビストロ UOKIN はなれ

tip.text: You are glad to have panoramic view mode in your iPhone at this rooftop terrace.
Sit on the kitchen counter and entertain your eyes with series of pizza cooked into perfection.
Every skewers great but neck is the must. And smoke cheese. After everything, you must close with sea urchin rice.
Specialized for wild turtle. Dinner course is great but a bit high end. Lunch is reasonable and you can enjoy Japanese style risotto with rich soup of wild turtle.

location.crossStreet: ソワレド銀座弥生ビルＢ１Ｆ
formattedAddress: 銀座7-6-19 (ソワレド銀座弥生ビルＢ１Ｆ)

tip.text: Sea urchin rolled with roast beef. Treat to your mouth. Open 4-8pm only but always full. Many good ones run out quickly even by 6.

formattedAddress: 勝どき1-8-1 (勝どきビュータワー 1F)

tip.text: Bowl is great. Pick standard one. Too much twist is often too much. Enjoy sun at terrace seat by drinking michelada.

formattedAddress: 8905 Melrose Ave (at N La Peer Dr)

tip.text: Many dishes continuously change. Hard to imagine what each dish taste like from menu. Best ask for chefs table at booking.
All the vegetable are great but ceviche at starter is unforgettable. Wait the queue by drinking healthy green smoothie.

formattedAddress: 35 E 18th St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave S)

tip.text: Hard to book but can walk in and wait by drinking at terrace. Everything taste great but follow the reco. Bone marrow is great with spinach pasta under that.
When you need something greasy but tasty on Sunday in the morning. Amen.
What's this refreshing flavor? Coriander and mustard? Capellini was really fantastic. You will surprise by tasting it as it's not like typical pasta taste. In good way.
Crostini is indeed great. No question. Mushroom w truffle oil and 2 prosciutto ones. Was torn between beef carpaccio or octopus. Octopus was never wrong choice. Next brunch for carpaccio.
Smoothie here makes perfect start of the day. Great choices but still my best is Acai Miracle.
Day pass at $50...but still worth visiting as entertainment. And of course good exercise. They have all the great machines.
Cheese toast...don't underestimate saying its kids meal.
Big restaurant so somehow you can get the table by booking on the day.
Try salty red wine by glass.
Sipping wine, soaking in water and looking around spectacular view. Perfect weekend afternoon.
Seafood chowder is unique and tasty. somewhat feels the flavor of thai curry as well. but, the best is the crudo sampler and sea urchin.
Each ingridient has its own great taste. But you tasta the real greatness when all united as one in your mouth. Like jedi soldiers. MTFBWY.
This is where I fell in love with Blue Bottle Coffee....or Coffee.
My favorite steakhouse. No matter I go New York or Chicago...
Everything we ordered were tasty but I really enjoyed beef tartar.
Very friendly staff. The artichoke salad is something once coming back to order again.
they do pick up from the hotel. so convenient, quick and reasonable.
overlooking great view of ocean and casino over beautiful and relaxing poolside. gym next to the pool is also great.

formattedAddress: Hôtel Fairmont Monte Carlo (12, Avenue des Spélugues)

tip.text: angel hair pasta...reason to come back again.

formattedAddress: 勝どき1-8-1 (勝どきビュータワー 1F)
勝どき1-8-1 (勝どきビュータワー 1F)

tip.text: Salad with slice of foie gras is really good.
spare rib is famous but what makes me keep coming back is stir-fried chinese vegetable with ham and chili. go great with rice

formattedAddress: 富民路87号 | 87 Fumin Rd (巨鹿路 | Julu Rd)

tip.text: foie gras in ther cold cut plates is great. pizza restaurant next to FRANCK is also really good.
Spending time in the terrace in autumn is great here.

location.address: URBN Hotel, 183 Jiaozhou Rd | 胶州路183号
formattedAddress: URBN Hotel, 183 Jiaozhou Rd | 胶州路183号 (Beijing Rd)

tip.text: Best spot in the hot summer Shanghai afternoon.

location.address: Silver Court Builing 6th Floor No.228 South Xizhang Rd
formattedAddress: Silver Court Builing 6th Floor No.228 South Xizhang Rd

tip.text: Great Pizza. Terrace lunch, no matter weekend or week day are especially good.

formattedAddress: Unit D, No. 2967, Lujiazui W Rd, (Binjiangda Dao)
location.address: Unit D, No. 2967, Lujiazui W Rd,

tip.text: Razor clam is one of the best dish in Shanghai for sure. Lunch course is also great and changes every month.

formattedAddress: G/F, The Waterhouse at South Bund, 1-3 Maojiayuan Rd. (btwn Waima Rd. & Zhongshan Rd. S)
location.crossStreet: btwn Waima Rd. & Zhongshan Rd. S
location.address: G/F, The Waterhouse at South Bund, 1-3 Maojiayuan Rd.

tip.text: Cool tapas place. Truffle pasta was really good.
All the fish dishes were great but I especially enjoyed razor clam.
